		<div class="col-sm-10">
			<h5>Knird ("Knird," "we," "us," or "our") believes your privacy is just that: yours. That means you have 
				absolute control over what you share on the Knird website (<%= link_to "www.drinkknird.com", root_path %>) 
				and through related services ("Services"). Knird will only ask for information from you if it is 
				explicitly related to our Service. In all cases, every time you provide personal information it 
				will be with your full consent and understanding. With that in mind, this privacy policy explains 
				what types of information you might provide while using our Services and how we could use that 
				information.</h5>
			<h3>Personal Information We Collect or You May Provide</h3>
			<h5>You provide the following personal information when you sign up with Knird:</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Your name</li>
					<li>Your email address</li> 
					<li>Your billing/home address</li>
					<li>Your credit card</li>
					<li>Your mobile phone number</li>
					<li>A delivery address, if different from your billing/home address</li>
					<li>Information related to your personal drink preferences</li>
				</ul>
			<h3>How We Use Your Personal Information</h3>
			<h5>We may use your personal information to:</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>Register you on Knird and identify you when you log in to our Service</li>
					<li>Respond to your questions, comments, requests, and complaints related to our Service</li>
					<li>Conduct research and analyze data to improve the user experience of our Service</li>
					<li>Send you confirmations, updates, security alerts, and support related to our Service</li>
					<li>Aggregate and anonymize data to analyze drink ordering opportunities</li>
					<li>Notify you of specific drinks available that should appeal to your specific taste preferences</li>
					<li>Ensure we are delivering the service promised to our users</li>
					<li>Communicate with you</li> 
				</ul>
			<h3>How We Share Your Personal Information with Third Parties</h3>
			<h5>We will share your personal information with third parties only in the ways that are described in this 
				privacy policy. We do not sell your Personal Information to third parties.</h5>
			<h5>We may share your Personal information in the following ways:</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>When we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your 
						safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.</li>
					<li>As required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process</li>
					<li>To enforce or apply our privacy policy or our terms of use</li>
				</ul>
			<h3>How We Store and Protect Your Personal Information</h3>
			<h5>We may store your personal information in locations outside our direct control, such as on servers or 
				databases managed by hosting providers.</h5>
			<h5>We take seriously the responsibility to safeguard your personal information. We follow generally accepted 
				standards to protect the personal information submitted to us, both during transmission and once we 
				receive it. However, no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage, is 
				100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. If you have any questions about our 
				security procedures, please <a href="mailto:questions@drinkknird.com">contact us</a>.</h5>
			<h5>Should a security breach take place, we will promptly notify anyone whose personal information is 
				compromised. That said, Knird does not accept liability for any unintentional disclosure or a disclosure 
				that occurs due to a security breach of our systems or facilities.</h5>
			<h3>Your opt-out rights</h3>
			<h5>You can stop all collection of information by our Service at any time by closing your Knird account.</h5>
			<h3>Our policy toward minors</h3>
			<h5>Knird is not directed to individuals under 21 and we do not use the Service to knowingly solicit data 
				from or market to individuals under the age of 21.  If you are a parent or guardian and believe your 
				under-18-year-old child has provided information to us without your consent, please 
				<a href="mailto:support@drinkknird.com">contact us</a> and we will delete such information from our files as 
				soon as possible.</h5>
			<h3>Your consent</h3>
			<h5>By using the Knird service, you are consenting to our processing of your information as set forth in 
				this privacy policy now and as amended by us. "Processing" means using cookies on a computer/hand 
				held device or using or touching information in any way, including, but not limited to, collecting, 
				storing, deleting, using, combining and disclosing information, all of which activities will take 
				place in the United States. If you reside outside the United States your information will be 
				transferred, processed and stored under United States privacy standard.</h5>
			<h3>Changes</h3>
			<h5>All information collected is subject to the privacy policy in effect at that time. However, this privacy 
				policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. We will notify you of any material changes to 
				our privacy policy by posting the new privacy policy here and informing you via email or in-application 
				message. You are advised to consult this privacy policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is 
				deemed approval of all changes.</h5>
			<h3>Questions?</h3>
			<h5>Please <a href="mailto:questions@drinkknird.com">contact us</a> if you have any questions about our 
				privacy policy.</h5><br>
			<h5>Effective: September 27, 2017</h5><br>
